<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: How do bypass the SNES audio low pass filter on the pcb?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12025&amp;p=136515#p136515"><![CDATA[
There are SPC equivalents made in FPGA, I think Kevtris made one, and there's also one by some Japanese guy.<br /><br />As far as OPN family FM chips go, the waveform is not 1 bit, it is log-transformed 12bit quartersine, that is converted to linear 14bit output, then mixed with other channels to get 16bit final output.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3483">TmEE</a> — Sun Nov 16, 2014 6:51 am</p><hr />
